    "text": "Erdős Problem #468: declared status 'open'. Formalized: no. For any $n$ let $D_n$ be the set of sums of the shape $d_1,d_1+d_2,d_1+d_2+d_3,\\ldots$ where $1<d_1<d_2<\\cdots$ are the divisors of $n$.\n\nWhat is the size of $D_n\\backslash \\cup_{m<n}D_m$?\n\nIf $f(N)$ is the minimal $n$ such that $N\\in D_n$ then is it true that $f(N)=o(N)$? Perhaps just for almost all $N$? Prize: no. OEIS: A167485, A387502, A387503. Tags: divisors, number theory.",
